place.name: STRUBBY
place.gazetteerText: STRUBBY-WITH-WOODTHORPE, a parish in Louth district, Lincoln; 4 miles N by E of Alford r. station. Post town, Alford. Acres, 2,075. Real property, £3,454. Pop., 295. Houses, 67. The property is subdivided. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £150. Patrons, the Dean and Chapter of L. The church, excepting the chancel, was rebuilt in 1857. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
